[{"id":"VH986079","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH865894.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The hyperbole in the closing sentence (lines 23-24) best conveys the speaker’s</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH986079_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"compose_cluster_phrase type:ordinal\"></span>  Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</p><p class=\"introduction passage-intro\">This poem was written by American poet John Frederick Nims (1913–1999).</p><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"poetry style:1\"><div class=\"title\"><p class=\"title_line passage-title\">Dedication: Love Poem</p></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My clumsiest dear, whose hands shipwreck vases,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>At whose quick touch all glasses chip and ring,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Whose palms are bulls in china, burs in linen,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And have no cunning with any soft thing</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Except all ill-at-ease fidgeting people:</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The refugee uncertain at the door</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>You make at home; deftly you steady</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The drunk clambering on his undulant floor.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Unpredictable dear, the taxi drivers’ terror,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Shrinking from far headlights pale as a dime</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Yet leaping before red apoplectic streetcars—</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Misfit in any space. And never on time.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>A wrench in clocks and the solar system. Only</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>With words and people and love you move at ease;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>In traffic of wit expertly manoeuvre</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And keep us, all devotion, at your knees,</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Forgetting your coffee spreading on our flannel,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Your lipstick grinning on our coat,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>So gayly in love’s unbreakable heaven</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Our souls on glory of spilt bourbon float.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Be with me, darling, early and late. Smash glasses—</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I will study wry music for your sake.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>For should your hands drop white and empty</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>All the toys of the world would break.</span><br/></div><span class=\"mandatory_credit_block\"><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">“Dedication: Love Poem” from <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Selected Poems</span> by John Frederick Nims. © 1982 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved.</span></span></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">distress at imagining the beloved’s death</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">criticism of the beloved’s many shortcomings</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">attempt to persuade the beloved to be more careful</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">satirical humor in relating the beloved’s characteristics</p>"],"answer":1}]